oy | author-link =Roy Wallis  | title =Religion as Fun? The Rajneesh Movement | journal = Sociological Theory, Religion and Collective Action | pages =191\u2013224 | publisher = Queen's University, Belfast | year =1986 |postscript=<!--None-->}}, reprinted in {{harvnb|Aveling|1999|pp=129\u2013161}}.\n{{Refend}}\n\n=== Further reading ===\n{{Refbegin|colwidth=50em}}\n* {{Citation\n| last =Appleton\n| first =Sue\n| title =Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh: The Most Dangerous Man Since Jesus Christ\n| publisher =Rebel Publishing House\n|  location =Cologne\n| isbn =3-89338-001-9\n| year =1987 }}.\n* {{Citation\n| last =Bharti\n| first =Ma Satya\n| title =Death Comes Dancing: Celebrating Life With Bhagwan Shree Rajneesh\n| publisher =[[Routledge]]\n| location =London, Boston, MA and Henley\n| isbn =0-7100-0705-1\n| year =1981\n| url =https://archive.org/details/deathcomesdancin00saty\n}}.\n* {{Citation\n| last =Bharti Franklin\n| first =Satya\n| title =The Promise of Paradise: A Woman's Intimate Story of the Perils of Life With Rajneesh\n| publisher =Station Hill Press\n| location =Barrytown, NY\n| isbn =0-88268-136-2\n| year =1992\n| url =https://archive.org/details/promiseofparadis00saty\n}}.\n* {{Citation\n| last =Braun\n| first =Kirk\n| title =Rajneeshpuram: The Unwelcome Society\n| publisher =Scout Creek Press\n|  location =West Linn, OR\n| isbn =0-930219-00-7\n| year =1984 }}.\n* {{Citation\n| last =Brecher\n| first =Max\n| title =A Passage to America\n| publisher =Book Quest Publishers\n| year =1993\n| location =Mumbai, India }}.\n* {{Citation\n| last =FitzGerald\n| first =Frances\n| authorlink =Frances FitzGerald (journalist)\n| title =Cities on a Hill: A Journey Through Contemporary American Cultures\n| publisher =[[Simon & Schuster]]\n| location =New York, NY\n| isbn =0-671-55209-0\n| year =1986 }}. (Includes a 135-page section on [[Rajneeshpuram]] previously published in two parts in ''[[The New Yorker]]'' magazine, 22 September, and 29 September 1986 editions.)\n* {{Cit